name: particleboard production, uncoated, from virgin wood | particleboard, uncoated | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/23651/documentation

This dataset represents particleboard production (uncoated), for indoor use (furniture industry), from virgin wood (eucalyptus species). This dataset was extrapolated from the Brazilian dataset of the same name. Default properties of the products are kept.

From reception of raw materials at the factory gate. Includes the inputs to the production processes and the main process emissions.

Until and including loading of the product on lorries. Capital goods, such as industrial machinery and infrastructure, as well as personnel activities, for instance, transport of workers to and from the workplace, were not included within the system boundary.
category: C:Manufacturing/16:Manufacture of wood and of products of wood and cork, except furniture; manufacture of articles of straw and plaiting materials/162:Manufacture of products of wood, cork, straw and plaiting materials/1621:Manufacture of veneer sheets and wood-based panels

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Average of data from Germany and Brazil.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Particleboard production is characterized by the use of wood coming from dedicated eucalyptus plantations. The main activities included in the industrial production are: reception and storage of wood logs; production, drying and classification of particles; blending; mat forming and pressing; and finishing.  Stored wood logs are debarked and chips and flakes are produced using choppers and ring flakers. The wood particles are then dried and classified. The larger particles form the internal layer of the panel, while the smaller ones are incorporated in the external layers. Bark and other wood residues from the manufacturing process as well as heavy fuel oil are burned to produce hot gas for particle drying and hot pressing processes. The dried particles are then blended with the synthetic adhesive and a mat of glued particles is made using feeding machines which form the three layers of the panel. The next steps are the pre-pressing and hot pressing (160-200ÂºC) of the mat to consolidate the panel. Afterwards, the panel is cut to the final dimensions and sanded.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: see Geography and Technology This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography BR. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography BR.
